channel.title: Compiler yes like the 50'th one you've read
channel.description: ok now im not a noob or leacher. i know how to code java. the only thing i cant figure out is why my compiler on project 16 isnt working. it says all the most repetitive stuff like 'javac can not be found' and 'cannot find specified path'. so does the place where you downloaded it to matter in the path?

item.title: Compiler yes like the 50'th one you've read
item.dc:creator: @aber aber
item.description:
@aber wrote:

edit your compile with this code

@echo off title your server name Compiler color B "C:\Program Files\java\jdk1.5.0_09\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_09\bin\java.exe" server pause

just change the your server name to any name you wish to make sure you have JDK 1.5.0.09

after you do that i 100% sure that you will not have problem again
